verses.text_plain: I lifted up mine eyes again, and looked, and behold a man with a measuring line in his hand.
verses.verse_html: 1I lifted up mine eyes again, and looked, and behold a man with a measuring line in his hand.

verses.text_plain: Then said I, Whither goest thou? And he said unto me, To measure Jerusalem, to see what is the breadth thereof, and what is the length thereof.
verses.verse_html: 2Then said I, Whither goest thou? And he said unto me, To measure Jerusalem, to see what is the breadth thereof, and what is the length thereof.

verses.text_plain: And, behold, the angel that talked with me went forth, and another angel went out to meet him,
verses.verse_html: 3And, behold, the angel that talked with me went forth, and another angel went out to meet him,

verses.text_plain: And said unto him, Run, speak to this young man, saying, Jerusalem shall be inhabited as towns without walls for the multitude of men and cattle therein:
verses.verse_html: 4And said unto him, Run, speak to this young man, saying, Jerusalem shall be inhabited as towns without walls for the multitude of men and cattle therein:

verses.text_plain: For I, saith the Lord, will be unto her a wall of fire round about, and will be the glory in the midst of her.
verses.verse_html: 5For I, saith the Lord, will be unto her a wall of fire round about, and will be the glory in the midst of her.

tokens.text: will be unto her a wall

verses.text_plain: Ho, ho, come forth, and flee from the land of the north, saith the Lord: for I have spread you abroad as the four winds of the heaven, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 6Ho, ho, come forth, and flee from the land of the north, saith the Lord: for I have spread you abroad as the four winds of the heaven, saith the Lord.

tokens.text: for I have spread you abroad

verses.text_plain: Deliver thyself, O Zion, that dwellest with the daughter of Babylon.
verses.verse_html: 7Deliver thyself, O Zion, that dwellest with the daughter of Babylon.

verses.text_plain: For thus saith the Lord of hosts; After the glory hath he sent me unto the nations which spoiled you: for he that toucheth you toucheth the apple of his eye.
verses.verse_html: 8For thus saith the Lord of hosts; After the glory hath he sent me unto the nations which spoiled you: for he that toucheth you toucheth the apple of his eye.

verses.text_plain: For, behold, I will shake mine hand upon them, and they shall be a spoil to their servants: and ye shall know that the Lord of hosts hath sent me.
verses.verse_html: 9For, behold, I will shake mine hand upon them, and they shall be a spoil to their servants: and ye shall know that the Lord of hosts hath sent me.

tokens.text: upon them, and they shall be a spoil

verses.text_plain: Sing and rejoice, O daughter of Zion: for, lo, I come, and I will dwell in the midst of thee, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 10Sing and rejoice, O daughter of Zion: for, lo, I come, and I will dwell in the midst of thee, saith the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And many nations shall be joined to the Lord in that day, and shall be my people: and I will dwell in the midst of thee, and thou shalt know that the Lord of hosts hath sent me unto thee.
verses.verse_html: 11And many nations shall be joined to the Lord in that day, and shall be my people: and I will dwell in the midst of thee, and thou shalt know that the Lord of hosts hath sent me unto thee.

tokens.text: of thee, and thou shalt know

verses.text_plain: And the Lord shall inherit Judah his portion in the holy land, and shall choose Jerusalem again.
verses.verse_html: 12And the Lord shall inherit Judah his portion in the holy land, and shall choose Jerusalem again.

verses.text_plain: Be silent, O all flesh, before the Lord: for he is raised up out of his holy habitation.
verses.verse_html:
13Be silent, O all flesh, before the Lord: for he is raised up out of his holy habitation.
 his: Heb. the habitation of his holiness
